content.description:
P1. 5.10-. A tricky start leads to fun, easy climbing on edges up to the anchors shared with

Obtuse Dilemma

.

TR Variation 5.12a/b: start just right of the arete, head up past a hard boulder problem, then follow the arete connecting with Winter's edge at the third bolt.
content.location: This is left of the arete above the parking area.

content.description:
Obtuse Dilemma has challenging stemming up a flaring dihedral. It keeps your attention!

P1) 5.11d: climb a short flake to a stance, then decipher the continuous, thin stemming to the fourth bolt followed by easier rock to the anchors.
content.location: This ascends the dihedral above the parking area.

content.description:
This route climbs the triangular face directly behind the parking area to a large ledge then continues up the slab above. Bring your edging shoes! It would get three stars if it wasn't for the ledge in the middle.

P1. 5.11c. Climb the triangular face past the snake to its apex and the large ledge, 5.10a. It is best to belay here, as the crux is getting to the second bolt above the ledge. Figure out the techy boulder problem, then climb nice edges to another thin section getting to the last bolt. Lower from the chains.
content.location: This is directly above the parking area.
